<item>
            <title>[LU-4463] nobody calls wakeup for ptlrpc_request::rq_set_waitq</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4463</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This waitq is added by patch of &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=21938&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=21938&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/attachment.cgi?id=29247&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/attachment.cgi?id=29247&lt;/a&gt; (commit 4a51b7a88) and &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/attachment.cgi?id=30143&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/attachment.cgi?id=30143&lt;/a&gt; (commit 526e9c54), however, nobody will wakeup thread waiting on this queue, the reason that we didn&apos;t run into problem is probably because it&apos;s a timed wait (5 seconds).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
